al period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":6,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":15,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":60,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Heiton was born about 1322, in Heaton Norris, Lancashire, England. She had at least 1 daughter with Adam de Billinge. She died in Billinge, Lancashire, England."},"et":{"Abt 1322–":"umbes 1322–Surnud","1318–Male":"1318–Surnud","1341–1386":"1341–1386","1322–Female":"1322–Surnud","1337":"1337","Abt 1322":"umbes 1322","1322":"1322","1453":"1453","1386":"1386","1341":"1341","1382":"1382","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Billinge, Lancashire, England":"Billinge, Lancashire, England","Heaton Norris, Lancashire, England":"Heaton Norris, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1322–":"noin 1322–Kuollut","1318–Male":"1318–Kuollut","1341–1386":"1341–1386","1322–Female":"1322–Kuollut","1337":"1337","Abt 1322":"noin 1322","1322":"1322","1453":"1453","1386":"1386"